RRBS - Array Comparison for J20 Pathology

Emma Walker

29/06/2021

Introduction

Many of the entorhinal cortex samples were ran on both the methylation array and using RRBS technology so can be compared. NB these MAY NOT BE identical samples however.

This script looks at the overlap between sites on the two technologies for the regression results for the J20 ECX Pathology models.

Note that these results are PRE FILTERING.

There are 24 signifcant results for the regressions on the array data

There are 3493 signifcant results for the regressions on the RRBS data

Sites that are significant in both technologies

There are 2300 sites which are in both technologies and 0 sites which are significant using both technologies.

Sites that are significant in the array data

There are 3 sites which are significant for the array data and have corresponding locations for the RRBS data. 0 of the corresponding sites in the array data are significant using bonferonni correction or using FDR adjustment.

Sites that are significant in the RRBS data

There are 5 sites which are significant for the RRBS data and have corresponding locations for the array data. 0 of the corresponding sites in the array data are significant using bonferonni correction or using FDR adjustment.
